  "response": "The number of credits you must take for the 2nd semester in VIT (Vellore Institute of Technology) can vary depending on your specific program and the curriculum structure. However, I can give you a general idea and how to find the exact information:\n\n**General Idea:**\n\n*   Typically, VIT (Vellore) follows a CBCS (Choice Based Credit System).\n*   A standard semester load usually ranges from **18 to 24 credits**.\n\n**How to find the exact information for your specific program:**\n\n1.  **VIT Academic Regulations/Curriculum:**\n\n    *   **The most reliable source is the official academic regulations and curriculum document for your specific B.Tech program and year of admission.** You can usually find this on the VIT website.  Look for sections related to:\n        *   Credit requirements per semester\n        *   Course structure for your program\n        *   List of courses offered in the 2nd semester of your program\n\n2.  **VIT Website:**\n\n    *   Navigate to the VIT website, specifically the page for your department or school (e.g., School of Computing Science and Engineering, School of Mechanical Engineering, etc.).\n    *   Look for the curriculum or syllabus section.\n    *   You should find a detailed breakdown of the courses offered in each semester, along with their corresponding credit values.\n\n3.  **VIT i-Learn Portal:** (Students Only)\n\n    *   If you are a current student, log in to the VIT i-Learn portal.\n    *   You should be able to view your registered courses and their credit values for the semester.\n\n4.  **Contact your Faculty Advisor/Program Coordinator:**\n\n    *   If you have trouble finding the information online, reach out to your faculty advisor or the program coordinator for your department.  They can provide the most accurate and up-to-date information about credit requirements.\n\n**Example:**\n\nLet's say you're a student in B.Tech Computer Science and Engineering (CSE).  You might find a table in the curriculum document that looks something like this (this is just an example):\n\n| Course Code | Course Title                       | Credits |\n| :---------- | :--------------------------------- | :------ |\n| CSE1002     | Problem Solving and Programming     | 3       |\n| MAT1011     | Calculus for Engineers           | 4       |\n| PHY1002     | Physics for Computer Engineers      | 3       |\n| CHY1003     | Environmental Science and Sustainability | 2       |\n| ENG1001     | Effective Communication Skills     | 3       |\n| CSE1901     | Technical Seminar                  | 1       |\n|             | Elective Course                   | 3       |\n| **Total**   |                                    | **19**   |\n\nIn this example, you would need to take a minimum of 19 credits in the 2nd semester.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Minimum and Maximum Credits:** VIT usually has a minimum and maximum number of credits you are allowed to take in a semester. Make sure you stay within these limits.\n*   **Prerequisites:** Ensure that you meet all the prerequisites for the courses you want to register for.\n*   **Electives:** If your curriculum includes elective courses, choose them carefully to meet your interests and program requirements.\n\n**In summary, the exact number of credits you need to take for the 2nd semester depends on your specific program at VIT. Refer to the official curriculum documents or contact your faculty advisor for the most accurate information.**\n",
